</taxonomicName>
species subgroup, new
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1374,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1374,1400]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Phallapodeme shorter than 1/2 of phallal sheath (ch.47-1; 
<figureCitation box="[935,1086,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11D,F,H</figureCitation>
). Distal portion of oviscapt not distinctly differentiated from basal portion (ch.50-1; 
<figureCitation box="[742,844,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="17.[151,250,762,786]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,182,734]" captionTargetId="figure-18@17.[151,1435,181,737]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 12. Characters 48‒51 on the female terminalia of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, hypoproct in ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, hypoproct in ventral view). Abbreviations: epiprct, epiproct; hyprct, hypoproct; ov, oviscapt; t-VIII, tergite VIII. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766426/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1374,1869]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,430,1446,1473]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Shared characters.</emphasis>
All coxae and femora dark brown to black at least partly, except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda, 2021" authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Colocasiomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Colocasiomia sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[278,367,1483,1509]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[278,367,1483,1509]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; all tibiae distally dark brown to black; all tarsi brownish yellow, with darker tarsomere V (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,860,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-242@21.[151,1435,860,1912]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Habitus (upper, lateral view; lower, dorsal view) of species of the Colocasiomyia cristata subgroup.A, C. ecornuta sp. nov. ♂; B, C. grandis sp. nov. ♂; C, C. vieti sp. nov. ♂; D, C. cristata de Meijere ♂; E, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso ♂; F, C. kinabaluana sp. nov. ♂; G, C. kotana sp. nov. ♂; and H, C. matthewsi sp. nov. ♂. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766434" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766434/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Fore tarsomere II with 4 pegs (ch.14-2; 
<figureCitation box="[666,756,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,250,903,927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,878]" captionTargetId="figure-22@12.[151,1435,181,879]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Characters 13‒15 on the fore (A, B, distal portion of tibia and tarsus) and mid (C, D, ditto) legs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, C) and C. cristata de Meijere (B, D). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766416/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Male abdominal sternite V wider than long (ch.18-0; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,987,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-64@12.[151,1435,987,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Characters 16‒22 on the male (A, C) and female (B, D) abdominal sternites (s) of Colocasiomyia gigantea (Okada) (A, B) and C. colocasiae (Duda) (C, D). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766418/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Epandrium without seta as long as width of epandrium on posteroventral margin (ch.31-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1216,1340,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10C,F</figureCitation>
). Cercus narrower than 1/2 cercal length; ventral/apical portion more or less differentiated from upper portion (ch.38,39-0; 
<figureCitation box="[151,275,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1695,1719]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-299@14.[151,1435,885,1672]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Characters 30‒39 on the periphallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, anterior view), C. cristata de Meijere (C, lateral view; D, ventral view; E, surstylus) and C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (F, oblique lateral view; G, ventral view; H, surstylus). Abbreviations: cerc, cercus; epand, epandrium; sur, surstylus. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766422/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 10C,F</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath apically not bilobed (ch.42-0; 
<figureCitation box="[797,947,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11D,F,H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
